import pydicom # for reading dicom files
import os # for doing directory operations 
import pandas as pd # for some simple data analysis (right now, just to load in the labels data and quickly reference it)
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import csv

data_dir = '/Users/emilyanaya/Documents/cs230/dicom_sample/'
patients = os.listdir(data_dir)
os.chdir(data_dir)

for i in range(len(patients)):
    ds = pydicom.dcmread(patients[i])

    #          the first slice
    plt.imshow(ds.pixel_array)
    plt.show()

data_dir = '/Users/emilyanaya/Documents/cs230'
os.chdir(data_dir)
any_hem = []
with open('stage_1_train.csv') as csvfile:
    readCSV = csv.reader(csvfile)
    readCSV = list(readCSV)
    for row in readCSV[:1000]:
        name, label = row
    
        if "any" in name:
            any_hem.append([name, label])
print(any_hem)
